        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 14 at 2:09PM EDT until May 14 at 2:45PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 209 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Hitesburg, or
near Virgilina, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind damage to
trees and powerlines.

This severe storm will be near...
Buffalo Springs around 215 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Nelson,
Spanish Grove, Richardson, Buffalo Junction, Finchley, Eppes Fork,
John H Kerr Reservoir, and Skipwith.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain alert for a possible tornado! Tornadoes can develop quickly
from severe thunderstorms. If you spot a tornado go at once into the
basement or small central room in a sturdy structure.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
